<img class="wp-image-1211459 aligncenter" src="https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila-300x239.jpg" alt="Gbajabiamila Congratulates Bello, Lyon" width="555" height="442" srcset="https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila-300x239.jpg 300w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila-58x46.jpg 58w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila-244x194.jpg 244w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila-163x130.jpg 163w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila-560x446.jpg 560w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Femi-Gbajabiamila.jpg 702w" sizes="(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px" /> The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila has described universities in Nigeria has lacking the capabilities the country needed to steer it out of turbulence to the path of greatness. He said it is doubtful that the country can count on its national institutions of education to drive its development conversation like other great institution of research have done throughout the ages. Delivering a keynote address at the First Tunde Ponle Annual Lecture with the theme: Building a Truly 21st Century University; A Task Beyond Government, at the Olagunsoye Oyinlola Auditorium of the institution campus in Osogbo, he the responsibility of reversing the decline in the quality of the university is primarily that of the government. But quickly added that building the 21st century university, out of the many that spread across the country, is beyond the capacity of government alone. He, however, maintained that establishing more privately owned university that is out of the reach of the ordinary Nigerians is not the ultimate solution to the problem, but to face and discuss the solution pragmatically. Vanguard News Nigeria. Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi  Gbajabiamila has urged the different arms of government to make intentional efforts to promote the accessibility of persons with disabilities in the country. Gbajabiamila said this at an event to commemorate the International Day of Persons with Disabilities organised by the house on… December 4, 2019 In "News" The Vice President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo has called on alumni associations to assist government improve the standard of education in the country. October 14, 2017 In "News" ABUJA-Some academics and non-academic staff in leading Nigerian universities have kicked against the call for the establishment of more universities by the Executive Secretary of the National Universities Commission (NUC), Professor Abubakar Adamu Rasheed. January 21, 2017 In "News"